An **oval diamond eternity band** has oval-cut diamonds set all the way around the shank — no gap, no plain metal, continuous sparkle from every angle. Oval eternity bands are more difficult to produce than round eternity rings: they require matched sets of 8–14 identical oval diamonds and carry a clarity specification (H-I/SI1-SI2 for natural, F-G/VS2-SI1 for lab) that confuses first-time buyers. This guide covers every oval diamond eternity ring on Blue Nile, organized by metal and carat weight, with the complete lab-versus-natural price analysis across all carat tiers from 2ct through 9.5ct.

