## Oval Diamond Eternity Bands — Rose Gold

Rose gold is the widest oval diamond eternity ring collection on Blue Nile: eight natural carat weights (2–9.5ct) and eight lab carat weights (2–9.5ct), with 15 verified buyer reviews at every single listing. It is the most data-complete metal for any buying decision across the full carat range.

Rose gold has a functional advantage for daily-wear oval eternity bands: no rhodium replating, ever. The 14K rose gold alloy (copper + gold) is the color throughout — it does not rely on a surface coating. White gold's rhodium plating wears in 12–36 months; rose gold's copper alloy never fades. An oval lab grown diamond eternity band in rose gold, bought once, requires zero metal maintenance for life. See the [rose gold oval diamond engagement ring guide](/rose-gold-oval-diamond-engagement-ring) for the no-plate promise in full.

