## Oval Diamond Eternity Bands — Platinum

Platinum oval eternity rings are the correct choice when your oval engagement ring is in platinum. Unlike white gold, platinum does not use rhodium plating — it is naturally silver-white throughout. Over time, platinum develops a patina (a matte, slightly textured surface) as surface scratches accumulate. Most wearers appreciate the patina; jewelers can re-polish to original brightness on request.

Lab-grown platinum oval eternity bands are not currently available — the lab collection runs in gold metals only. Platinum oval eternity rings are available in 3ct, 4ct, 8ct, and 9.5ct natural. See the [platinum oval diamond engagement ring guide](/platinum-oval-diamond-engagement-ring) for the full case for and against platinum.

