## Full Eternity vs Half Eternity: Oval Diamond Band Comparison

An oval diamond half eternity band (also called a seven-stone oval band) has diamonds set only on the upper half, with plain metal on the lower shank. Full oval eternity bands have diamonds all the way around. The distinction matters for daily comfort, resizability, and price.

| Factor | Full Oval Eternity Band | Oval Half Eternity Band |
|--------|------------------------|------------------------|
| Stone coverage | All around (8–14 stones) | Top half only (7 stones) |
| Resizable | No | Yes |
| Entry price (lab) | $4,370 | $2,120 |
| Entry price (natural) | $4,494 | $2,681 |
| Bottom-of-finger feel | Stones present (adjustment period) | Plain metal (comfortable immediately) |
| Visibility from sides | Full sparkle | Tapers off toward shank |

For buyers whose size is confirmed: full eternity delivers the all-around sparkle that justifies its premium over the half-eternity style. For buyers with sizing uncertainty: a half-eternity (seven-stone) oval band at $2,120–$2,681 is the lower-risk choice. The complete half-eternity oval band range — including all seven-stone styles and the bezel seven-stone anniversary bands — is covered in the [oval diamond wedding band guide](/oval-diamond-wedding-band).

