## Carat Weight Selection Guide

The right carat weight for an oval diamond eternity ring depends on finger size, band-to-hand proportion, and how the band relates to your oval engagement ring if you're stacking.

**Finger size 4–5.5 (small hands):** 2ct–3ct total. At this finger circumference, a 2ct oval eternity ring covers the top half of the finger fully and reads as elegant without overpowering. The individual oval stones in a 2ct ring weigh approximately 0.15–0.22ct each.

**Finger size 6–6.5 (average):** 3ct–5ct total. Standard sizing. The [3ct RG lab at $5,100](https://www.bluenile.com/wedding-rings/oval-cut-lab-grown-diamond-eternity-ring-in-14k-rose-gold-3-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-259018?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the sweet spot: enough weight for clear oval coverage, under $5,500 lab, resale-neutral.

**Finger size 7+ (larger hands):** 5ct–9.5ct total. Larger circumferences need more total weight to achieve visual density. The [5ct RG lab at $6,280](https://www.bluenile.com/wedding-rings/oval-cut-lab-grown-diamond-eternity-ring-in-14k-rose-gold-5-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-259078?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the entry point where the band reads as a statement on larger hands.

**Pairing with a large oval engagement ring (2ct+):** The eternity band should not compete with the center stone for visual dominance. For a 2ct oval solitaire, a 2ct eternity band provides visual equilibrium — both carry equal weight. For 3ct+ oval engagement rings, a 1–2ct oval eternity band is proportionally correct: the solitaire remains clearly dominant. See the [oval diamond solitaire engagement ring guide](/oval-diamond-solitaire-engagement-ring) for proportion matching.

